The paper deals with kernelization for NP-hard problems on planar graphs, which suggests that it could belong to categories related to graph theory and computational complexity. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are all relevant sub-categories. Among these, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely as they deal directly with graph algorithms and structures, while cs.DM, cs.GT, and cs.CC are also relevant but may be slightly less likely as they are broader categories.
